'''Theodore Zachary Cotler''' (born 1981) is an American filmmaker, poet, and novelist. His first film, ''[[Maya Dardel]]'', premiered in the Narrative Competition at the 2017 [[South by Southwest]] Film Festival and was acquired by [[Samuel Goldwyn Films]] and [[Orion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/06/maya-dardel-movie-lena-olin-samuel-goldwyn-orion-sxsw-1202118266/|title=Samuel Goldwyn & Orion Acquire SXSW Pic ‘Maya Dardel’}}</ref> His second film, ''[[The Wall of Mexico]]'', premiered at [[South by Southwest]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://schedule.sxsw.com/2019/films/2009135|title=SXSW Schedule}}</ref> A third film, ''[[When I'm a Moth]]'', came out shortly after the second.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sffilm.org/event/when-im-a-moth/|title=San Francisco International Film Festival Schedule}}</ref> He won the 2012 [[Sawtooth Poetry Prize]] for ''Sonnets to the Humans'' and the 2104 [[Colorado Prize for Poetry]] for ''Supplice''.<ref name="colostate1">{{cite web|url=http://coloradoreview.colostate.edu/colorado-prize-for-poetry/current-winner/ |title=Current Winner &#124; Center for Literary Publishing |publisher=Coloradoreview.colostate.edu |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> In 2011, the [[Poetry Foundation]] awarded him the [[Ruth Lilly Fellowship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poetryfoundation.org/foundation/prizes_fellowship |title=Ruth Lilly Poetry Fellowships |publisher=The Poetry Foundation |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>

== Early life and education ==
Cotler spent his childhood in [[Marin County, California]]. He graduated from [[Cornell University]] in 2003 with a B.A. in English.<ref name="poetryfoundation1">{{cite web|url=http://www.poetryfoundation.org/bio/t-zachary-cotler |title=T. Zachary Cotler |publisher=The Poetry Foundation |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> In 2008, he received his MFA in poetry from the [[Iowa Writers Workshop]].<ref name="poetryfoundation1"/>

==Career==
In 2009, Cotler founded [[The Winter Anthology]] at winteranthology.com with Michael Rutherglen, Olivia Clare, and Brandon Krieg.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://winteranthology.com/?vol=4&page=masthead |title=The Winter Anthology — Masthead |publisher=Winteranthology.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> Cotler continues to spearhead and edit the anthology.<ref>{{cite web|author=Steven Toussaint |url=http://steventoussaint.blogspot.com/ |title=(to-forge-the-eye-is-a-mountain-in-the-empyrean) |publisher=Steventoussaint.blogspot.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> His first book of poems, ''House with a Dark Sky Roof'', was published in 2011. In 2012, [[Heather McHugh]] picked Cotler as the winner of the Sawtooth Prize, and in 2013, Ahsahta Press published ''Sonnets to the Humans'', a cycle of 49 sonnets (the first of a projected trilogy of such sequences).<ref>{{cite web|author=T. Zachary Cotler |url=https://ahsahtapress.org/product/sonnets-to-the-humans/ |title=Sonnets to the Humans &#124; Ahsahta PressAhsahta Press |publisher=Ahsahtapress.org |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>
''Supplice'', the second book of sonnets, was picked as the winner of the 2014 Colorado Prize for Poetry by [[Claudia Keelan]].<ref name="colostate1"/>
Cotler's first novel ''Ghost at the Loom'' was published in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Edward Stephens |url=http://bookslut.com/fiction/2014_03_020553.php |title=Ghost at the Loom by T. Zachary Cotler |publisher=Bookslut |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>
Cotler's first film, ''[[Maya Dardel]],'' starring [[Lena Olin]], [[Jordan Gavaris]], [[Alexander Koch (actor)|Alexander Koch]], [[Nathan Keyes]], and [[Rosanna Arquette]], was released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/festivals/sxsw-ansel-elgorts-baby-driver-world-premiere-1201974426/|website=Variety|title=SXSW Film Festival Announces 2017 Lineup}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6218440/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ov_st_sm|website=imdb|title=Maya Dardel}}</ref> Cotler and filmmaking partner [[Magdalena Zyzak]] received Best Screenplay for ''[[Maya Dardel]]'' at the [[Prague Independent Film Festival]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://prague.tv/en/s72/c8-Cinema/n10429-Train-Driver-s-Diary-wins-at-Prague-Independent-Film-Festival|publisher=Prague TV|title=Train Driver's Diary wins at Prague Independent Film Festival}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prague-film-festival.com/winners-2017.html|publisher=PIFF|title= PIFF 2017 Winners}}</ref> and Best Director for ''[[Maya Dardel]]'' at the 2017 [[Raindance Film Festival]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.raindance.org/award-winners-raindance-film-festival-2017/|publisher=Raindance|title=Cotler and Zyzak win Best Director.}}</ref>

